request.description:
### CreateObjectOperations

This endpoint is used to create object operations with the provided parameters.

#### Request Body

- `jsonrpc` (string): The JSON-RPC version.

- `method` (string): The method name, in this case, "CreateObjectOperations".

- `id` (string): The ID of the request.

- `params` (array): An array of parameters containing the ticket, version, and operations details.


Example:

``` json
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "CreateObjectOperations",
  "id": "33",
  "params": [
    {
      "Ticket": "{{Current_Ticket}}",
      "HaveVersion": {
        "ID": "13129",
        "Version": "0.18",
        "__classname__": "ObjectVersion"
      },
      "Operations": [
        {
          "Id": "10be2025-9e15-4a4d-8af0-899808b9b03a",
          "Name": "ClearFrameContent",
          "Type": "AutomatedPrintWorkflow",
          "Params": [
            {
              "Name": "EditionId",
              "Value": 0,
              "__classname__": "Param"
            },
            {
              "Name": "SplineId",
              "Value": 703,
              "__classname__": "Param"
            }
          ],
          "__classname__": "ObjectOperation"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

 ```

#### Response

- `id` (string): The ID of the response.

- `result` (object): The result object containing operations and reports.

    - `Operations` (array): An array of operations with their details.

    - `Reports` (array): An array of reports.

    - `__classname__` (string): The class name of the result object.

- `jsonrpc` (string): The JSON-RPC version.


Example:

``` json
{
  "id": "",
  "result": {
    "Operations": [
      {
        "Id": "",
        "Name": "",
        "Type": "",
        "Params": [
          {
            "Name": "",
            "Value": 0,
            "__classname__": ""
          }
        ],
        "__classname__": ""
      }
    ],
    "Reports": [],
    "__classname__": ""
  },
  "jsonrpc": ""
}

 ```

